response.job_title: Mechanical Engineer | CAD | Data Engineering | Python | SQL | Azure | Databricks
response.summary: As a mechanical engineer with 3 years of experience, I have successfully transitioned into the exciting field of data engineering. My fascination with the world of data and my problem-solving abilities drove me to focus on this thrilling field. I have a strong command of Python and its powerful libraries for data manipulation and analysis, as well as extensive knowledge of SQL for effective database management and querying. I am committed to continuous learning, staying updated with the latest trends and technologies in the field of data engineering. With a proactive attitude and a solid foundation in Python and SQL, I am excited to apply my skills and continue growing in this captivating field of data engineering.

company.name: Datalytics
company.description:
We are a consulting firm that turns data into information.

For the past 15 years, we have worked to democratize data so that people can make better decisions.

At Datalytics, we like to define ourselves as the university of data because we are the best place in the region to develop a career related to big data.

We are technology agnostic, we use our own technology and we also learn and use all innovations in big data to offer unique and cutting-edge services.

We have an open, inclusive, challenging culture, characterized by collaboration and continuous learning.
We are an interdisciplinary team of talents composed of more than 200 people with clients in LATAM, the US, and Europe.

In addition, we have offices in Argentina, Colombia, and Spain. 

We are sure that it is always best with data.
